This paper is about intrusion detection systems (ids) and their use of Snort rules to detect suspicious or unacceptable system and network activity. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as generalisation and specialisation, which suggests that it could also fit into categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves experiments with datasets, which could place it in categories such as cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
